    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You need to make sure that prysm can \"talk\" to erigon via the `authrpc` connection, which means:\r\n\r\n- you generate a shared secret for both of them, a file called `jwt.hex` and copy it to each client's datadir\r\n- erigon should open port 8551 for communication, but you might need to add `--authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0` and `--authrpc.vhosts=*` so that prysm can reach it\r\n- and for prysm you add `--execution-endpoint=http://localhost:8551`\r\n\r\nMore options are available for custom ports and custom paths or names of `jwt.hex` and of course you can find more about it in the documentation, e.g.: https://docs.prylabs.network/docs/execution-node/authentication",
